        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Problem 1. For "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "n \\geq 1"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", we consider the integral "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                112,
                190,
                447,
                205
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "I _ {n} = \\int_ {[ 0, 1 ] ^ {n}} \\frac {n}{\\frac {1}{x _ {1}} + \\frac {1}{x _ {2}} + \\cdots + \\frac {1}{x _ {n}}} d x _ {1} \\dots d x _ {n}.",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/ca9a3734199d7aa3388ea3b8b02fa1ab47b6d9e9dd9b512154b3155db982d321.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                351,
                223,
                643,
                260
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Prove that "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\operatorname* { l i m } _ { n \\to \\infty } I _ { n }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "exists. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                112,
                275,
                284,
                294
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Problem 2. Let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "U \\subset \\mathbf { C }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "be a non-empty open set and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "f : U \\to U"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "be a non-constant holomorphic function. Prove that, if "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "f \\circ f = f"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", then "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "f ( z ) \\equiv z"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "for all "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "z \\in U"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                111,
                313,
                883,
                345
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Problem 3. Let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "X \\subset \\mathbf { R }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "be a set with positive (Lebesgue) measure. Show that we can find an arithmetic progression of 2022 terms in "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "X ,"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", i.e., there exists "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "x _ { 1 } , \\dots , x _ { 2 0 2 2 } \\in X"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "so that the "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "x _ { i + 1 } - x _ { i } { } ^ { \\circ } { \\mathrm { s } }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "are all equal and positive, "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "i = 1 , \\ldots , 2 0 2 1"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                111,
                366,
                883,
                415
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Problem 4. Let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "C ( [ 0 , 1 ] )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "be the space of all continuous ??-valued functions equipped with "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "L ^ { \\infty }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "-norm. Let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\textbf { P } \\subset"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "C ( [ 0 , 1 ] )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "be a closed linear subspace. Assume that the elements of "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\mathbf { P }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "are polynomials. Prove that dim "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\mathbf { P } < \\infty"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                111,
                434,
                883,
                468
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Problem 5. Let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\Omega \\subset \\mathbf { R } ^ { 3 }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "be a bounded domain with smooth boundary. Assume that "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "u \\in C \\left( \\overline { { { \\bf R } ^ { 3 } - \\Omega } } \\right)"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is a harmonic function on "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\mathbf { R } ^ { 3 } - \\Omega"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "so that "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\boldsymbol { u } \\big | _ { \\Omega } = 1"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\operatorname* { l i m } _ { | x |  \\infty } | u ( x ) | = 0"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                111,
                489,
                883,
                531
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Prove that for such "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "u"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\operatorname* { l i m } _ { | x | \\to \\infty } | x | u ( x )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "exists. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                112,
                536,
                401,
                559
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Problem 6. Let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "f ( x , y ) \\in C ^ { 1 } ( \\mathbf { R } ^ { 2 } )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". We assume that there exists "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "C > 0"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "so that for all "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "( x , y ) \\in \\mathbf { R } ^ { 2 }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\begin{array} { r } { \\left| \\frac { \\partial f } { \\partial y } ( x , y ) \\right| \\le C } \\end{array}"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". Prove that the following ODE has a globally defined solution for all "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "y ( 0 ) = y _ { 0 } \\in \\mathbf { R }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ": "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                111,
                580,
                883,
                617
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\left\\{ \\begin{array}{l} \\frac {d}{d x} y (x) = f (x, y (x)), \\\\ y (0) = y _ {0}. \\end{array} \\right. \\tag {1}",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/6de0fe0f5b951750d06f5d41b31e22b4c857a141b6d69b36647160bc4cc321d2.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                410,
                633,
                883,
                678
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "In addition, we assume that "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "f"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is 1-periodic in "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "x"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", i.e., for all "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "( x , y ) \\in \\mathbf { R } ^ { 2 }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", we have "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "f ( x + 1 , y ) = f ( x , y )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". Prove that if (1) admits a globally defined bounded solution, then (1) admits a periodic solution. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                111,
